{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd23ba0e94a3c4025ac1", "type": "numerical", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "In the reaction of potassium dichromate, potassium chloride and sulfuric acid (conc.), the oxidation state of the chromium in the product is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mo>+</mo></mfenced></math>\u00a0_______.", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "6", "solution": {"text": "<p>The oxidation state or oxidation number is defined as the loss or gain of electrons from an atom, molecule, or compound.</p><p>The reaction of potassium dichromate, potassium chloride and sulphuric acid (conc.)is as follows,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>Cr</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>7</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>KCl</mi><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>conc</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u2192</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>CrO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><msub><mi>KHSO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math></p><p>This reaction takes place in\u00a0chromyl chloride test.</p><p>The Chromyl chloride is a neutral molecule\u00a0as it does not have any charge on it.</p><p>Here, oxidation state of\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Cr</mi></math>\u00a0 in\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CrO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> is\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ61135705", "subject": "Chemistry", "subjects": ["615d70bd9948bc1b21da2b1f"], "chapters": ["615d6fee2b295b085ab6ebc0"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c11d30997d3436bb05", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "numericalLowerLimit": 6, "numericalUpperLimit": 6, "classes": [], "microConcepts": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["615f0cf69476412f48314dac", "616057040283de43c87e3e16", "61bb58281213731910ea0b71", "6160579d0283de43c87e3e1f", "61964f94a5a526011886801e", "61c055f6e8ce0dc8a5c62d34", "61a8a2cce8ce0dc8a5c62d2e", "6160577e0283de43c87e3e1c", "616057210283de43c87e3e19", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352c", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd8", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7e", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625c", "61964ff3a5a5260118868022", "64d50c263df7f4a7f3017f70", "66b79b89d4b564dfab4f94d0", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc12", "67fa602f4468eb1307ceb0ae", "6807d350647479b8e869647a"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616024eae1fef5cf5a5f70c9", "616024edea835316cf9c2507", "616024eb5cd52bad3baecd60", "61e7bd76702e5d858115fa8a", "61964cb4b35a1a71da75d378", "616024eeacea1d46cf67614a", "61bb821a019d574b936779c2", "61c0899a9e16bde43a5db70d", "616024ed438772c9179f9f0c", "61964cb3ddf4d3b39bb3af0c", "62962118ad101b4bb5b180fb", "629f38ff99eb561f9184935c", "629109dba75ec29dcfffb307", "629f3a857b20d833b06eab9a", "64eb06ce3118f713ecfef10d", "66d5853ea75f05ee8564f592", "67921d741d5b5072da5e9b34", "67fdff4a378e1624ea7b69bb", "68091fe13a10446a207fdbde"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", 